channel.title: Compiler problems
channel.description:
I am making a RSPS and im not to new but i know how to code alot of things. my major weak point is compiling and that stuff. so i came here looking for help, i dont think this is the right area for this but whatever a mod can move if he/she wants. i manage a 317 delta called hybrid-scape, my base is corruptionV its a delta, i know its a delta and it shit, but im making a quick easy server while i finish my hyperion server.
[code] Code: [Select] Note: Some input files use or override a deprecated API. Note: Recompile with -Xlint:deprecation for details. Finished! Press any key to continue . . . [/code]
this is my coding inside my compiler. i have used other ones and i cant seem to get it to compile. [code]Code: [Select] @echo off if exist "%programfiles%\Java" (call :compile "%programfiles%\Java\") else (goto error) :compile for /D %%x in ("%~1jdk*") do (set p="%%~x\bin\javac.exe") if defined p (%p% -cp . *.java) if defined p (goto end) :error echo You do not have Java installed. Please download it at the site that is about to load. "%programfiles%\Internet Explorer\iexplore.exe" http://java.sun.com/javase/downloads/index.jsp :end echo Finished! pause exit [/code]
this is my clients compiler, my server has a fine compiler that works fine. and if i switch the codes it still says the same thing any help?
i can't get my server online till i fix this. any help would be amazing and i will love you forever.

item.title: Compiler problems
item.dc:creator: @Skiire Skiire
item.description:
@Skiire wrote:

buba753:

i feel like huge noob now xD but i added my ip and i got my no-ip running and shit but i go to log in and it says connection error. i compiled and i did everything. the server i based off the guy said worked fine and i just switched ip’s to get it working while i code it. any suggestions if i may ask?

It could be numerous things.

Possibilties:

[ul][li]You’re not portforwarded[/li]
[li]You’re using the wrong port[/li]
[li]You started the client before the server (sometimes)[/li]
[li]You’re using the wrong IP, use localhost.[/li][/ul]

Or something else that I’m just not thinking of right now.

item.title: Compiler problems
item.dc:creator: @Skiire Skiire
item.description:
@Skiire wrote:

Those “errors” are not really “errors” they’re warnings. You’re using deprecated API’s within some classes and your compiler is telling you this. It’s compiled fine and you have nothing to worry about though. If it’s really just bothering you, add this:

@SupressWarnings("deprecation")

To all classes which use deprecated terms.
